HEADWORD: Ankh
<hw>Ankh</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Egypt.]</ety>
<fld>(Egypt. Arch⟦ae⟧ol.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A tau cross with a loop
at the top, used as an attribute or sacred emblem, symbolizing
generation or enduring life. Called also <altname>crux
ansata</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>an amulet or piece of jewelry shaped like an
ankh{1}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ankle</ent>⟦br⟧
